nodes.bodyText:
I know this is written to match the spec, but I think we should try to implement this more efficiently.  There are a few O(n^2) loops here.  Suggest doing something like:
    NavigableSet<Eth1Data> votesToConsider = getVotesToConsider();
    Map<Eth1Data, Eth1Vote> validVotes = new HashMap<>();
    int index = 0;
    for (Eth1Data eth1Vote : state.getEth1_data_votes()) {
      if (!votesToConsider.contains(eth1Vote)) {
        continue;
      }
      Eth1Vote vote = votes.computeIfAbsent(key -> new Eth1Vote(eth1Vote));
      vote.incrementVotes();
      vote.setIndex(index);
      index++;
    }

    return validVotes.values()
      .stream()
      .max(Eth1Vote::compare)
      .orElse(votesToConsider.last());

